headline.main: ENGLAND.; Parliamentary Proceedings--The Cab Strike --The Times on the New-York Exhibition Miscellaneous News, &c

docs.lead_paragraph: Late sittings and hard work have been the order of the evening--and for that matter, the morning, too--in the House of Commons, during the past week. Honorable members work diligently from the same feeling as that which animates schoolboys when the hope of release is looming up at no great distance. About three weeks, or even less, will conclude the session; and hence the necessity of dispatching public business before partridge-shooting commences.

docs.lead_paragraph: The following extracts are from the Bermuda Royal Gazette of the 2d instant: A good deal of excitement has prevailed in the West India Islands subsequent to the receipt of the intelligence of the intention of the Imperial Government to withdraw the troops from the West Indies, and also of the intention of the Government to re duce the Ordnance and Commissariat establishments.
